    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-04T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-04T14:00:00-05:00" n="46"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d46">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/3809: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-04T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 4, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>429. The situation reported in your 582, April 2, 2 p.m. and 583, April 3, 10
                    a.m. has been discussed with the War Department which is requesting Stilwell to
                    take necessary steps to assure an improvement <pb facs="0065" n="51"
                        xml:id="pg_51"/> in liaison between his Headquarters and the Embassy. We are
                    confident that you will cooperate in effecting an improved liaison.</p>
                <p>Please avail yourself of every opportunity in your contacts with Chinese to allay
                    unfounded fears and suspicions mentioned in your reference telegrams.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
